{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "IndirectAerosolForcing",
        "description": "First indirect aerosol effect (Twomey effect): change in shortwave forcing from aerosol-induced increase in cloud droplet number concentration — Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 24 §24.8.2, Eqs. 24.42–24.43.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "radiative_forcing"
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "IndirectAerosolForcing": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, Chapter 24, Section 24.8.2, Equations 24.42–24.43.",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/aerosol_radiative_forcing.jl:306\nFirst indirect aerosol effect (Twomey/cloud-albedo effect). Aerosols acting as CCN increase cloud droplet number concentration N at fixed liquid water content, reducing mean droplet radius and increasing cloud optical depth and albedo. The Twomey susceptibility S = dR_c/d(ln N) = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 (Eq. 24.41) gives the change in cloud albedo per fractional change in N: ΔR_c = S * Δln_N (Eq. 24.42). Eq. 24.43 converts ΔR_c to a top-of-atmosphere shortwave forcing: ΔF_c = -F_0 * A_c * T_a² * ΔR_c. The negative sign reflects that increased cloud albedo cools by reflecting more incoming solar radiation.\n\nAfter MTK structural_simplify, the two algebraic equations reduce to zero ODE states — both ΔR_c and ΔF_c are pure observed bindings. The standalone model treats R_c as a fixed parameter (default 0.5, peak susceptibility); coupling with CloudAlbedo would promote R_c to a shared variable.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-8 / abs=1e-12): both outputs are short products of bounded dimensionless parameters. ΔR_c is a four-factor product (R_c, 1-R_c, 1/3, Δln_N); ΔF_c is a five-factor product (F_0, A_c, T_a², ΔR_c) — float64 roundoff accumulates to ~4 ULP, well within rel=1e-8. abs=1e-12 floors the Δln_N → 0 limit where both outputs vanish."
            },
            "variables": {
                "F_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 1370.0,
                    "description": "Incident solar flux"
                },
                "A_c": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.6,
                    "description": "Cloud fraction (dimensionless)"
                },
                "T_a": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.76,
                    "description": "Atmospheric transmittance (dimensionless)"
                },
                "R_c": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.5,
                    "description": "Cloud albedo (dimensionless). At R_c = 0.5 the Twomey susceptibility S = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 is maximised (1/12 ≈ 0.0833)."
                },
                "Δln_N": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.262,
                    "description": "Fractional change in cloud droplet number concentration, Δln(N) = ln(N₁/N₀) (dimensionless). Default ≈ ln(1.3): a 30% increase in CDNC."
                },
                "ΔR_c": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Change in cloud albedo from the Twomey effect: ΔR_c = R_c*(1−R_c)/3 * Δln_N — Eq. 24.42.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "R_c",
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    1,
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "*",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            -1,
                                                            "R_c"
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    3
                                ]
                            },
                            "Δln_N"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "ΔF_c": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "description": "Change in shortwave forcing from the first indirect aerosol effect: ΔF_c = −F_0 * A_c * T_a² * ΔR_c — Eq. 24.43. Negative = cooling (increased albedo reflects more solar radiation).",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            -1,
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "F_0",
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "A_c",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "^",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "T_a",
                                                            2
                                                        ]
                                                    },
                                                    "ΔR_c"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-8,
                "abs": 1e-12
            },
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "eq_24_43_default_30pct_cdnc_increase",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream Aerosol.jl 'Indirect Forcing - Section 24.8.2 Validation' testitem. At the canonical 30% CDNC increase (Δln_N = ln(1.3) ≈ 0.262), R_c = 0.5, F_0 = 1370 W/m², A_c = 0.6, T_a = 0.76: ΔR_c ≈ 0.02186 and ΔF_c ≈ −10.38 W/m². Upstream asserts ΔR_c ≈ 0.0219 rtol=0.05, ΔF_c < 0, |ΔF_c| ∈ (5, 20) W/m²; we pin the exact analytic float64 values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.021863688705624253
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -10.380599542214963
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 0.021863688705624253
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": -10.380599542214963
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_cdnc_change_no_forcing",
                    "description": "Boundary condition: Δln_N = 0 (no change in CDNC) yields ΔR_c = 0 and ΔF_c = 0 exactly — no cloud albedo change, no indirect forcing.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "linearity_double_delta_lnN",
                    "description": "Linearity check: doubling Δln_N doubles both ΔR_c and ΔF_c because both formulas are linear in Δln_N. At 2*ln(1.3) ≈ 0.5247, ΔR_c and ΔF_c are exactly twice the Δln_N=ln(1.3) values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.5247285289349821
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.043727377411248505
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -20.761199084429926
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "twomey_symmetry_low_albedo",
                    "description": "Twomey susceptibility symmetry: S(R_c) = R_c*(1-R_c)/3 is symmetric about R_c = 0.5, so S(0.1) = S(0.9). ΔR_c at R_c = 0.1 matches ΔR_c at R_c = 0.9 (within float64 roundoff).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.1,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.007870927934024732
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -3.7370158351973872
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "twomey_symmetry_high_albedo",
                    "description": "Twomey susceptibility symmetry: S(0.9) = S(0.1) = 0.1*0.9/3. ΔR_c and |ΔF_c| at R_c = 0.9 are equal to those at R_c = 0.1 (symmetric partner). Upstream asserts S(0.1) ≈ S(0.9) — we pin the exact analytic value.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.9,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.00787092793402473
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -3.7370158351973863
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "twomey_symmetry_quarter_and_threequarter",
                    "description": "Exact binary-fraction symmetry pair: R_c = 0.25 and R_c = 0.75 give identical ΔR_c = 0.25*0.75/3 * Δln_N (both are exact in float64). Confirms S(R_c) = S(1-R_c) for a rational symmetric pair.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.25,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.01639776652921819
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cloud_fraction_scaling",
                    "description": "Linear scaling with cloud fraction A_c: at A_c = 0.3 (half of default), |ΔF_c| is halved. Indirect forcing scales linearly with the fraction of sky covered by cloud.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.3,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.021863688705624253
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -5.190299771107481
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "solar_flux_scaling",
                    "description": "Linear scaling with incident solar flux F_0: at F_0 = 685 W/m² (half of default), |ΔF_c| is halved (ΔR_c is unchanged). Indirect forcing scales linearly with the available solar resource.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "F_0": 685.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔR_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.021863688705624253
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ΔF_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -5.190299771107481
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "indirect_forcing_vs_cdnc_change",
                    "description": "Indirect aerosol forcing ΔF_c as a function of fractional CDNC change Δln_N at the default parameters (R_c=0.5, F_0=1370 W/m², A_c=0.6, T_a=0.76). The linear Twomey relationship gives ΔF_c ≈ −10.4 W/m² for a 30% CDNC increase (Δln_N = ln(1.3) ≈ 0.262). Illustrates how the indirect forcing scales with the anthropogenic perturbation to cloud droplet number.",
                    "parameters": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "Δln_N",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.0,
                                    "stop": 0.6,
                                    "count": 60,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dF_c_vs_delta_lnN",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Indirect shortwave forcing ΔF_c (W/m²) as a function of fractional CDNC change Δln_N. The linear relationship reflects the Twomey susceptibility; cooling (negative ΔF_c) increases with CDNC perturbation.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "Δln_N",
                                "label": "Fractional CDNC change Δln(N)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ΔF_c",
                                "label": "Indirect forcing ΔF_c (W/m²)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cloud_albedo_change_vs_Rc",
                    "description": "Change in cloud albedo ΔR_c as a function of background cloud albedo R_c at fixed Δln_N = ln(1.3) ≈ 0.262 (30% CDNC increase). The parabolic Twomey susceptibility S = R_c*(1−R_c)/3 peaks at R_c = 0.5, so clouds with intermediate albedo respond most strongly to aerosol perturbations. Connects to the CloudAlbedoSensitivity component.",
                    "parameters": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "A_c": 0.6,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "R_c",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.01,
                                    "stop": 0.99,
                                    "count": 60,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dR_c_vs_R_c",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Cloud albedo change ΔR_c as a function of background cloud albedo R_c. The symmetric parabola peaks at R_c = 0.5 (maximum Twomey susceptibility) and vanishes at R_c = 0 and R_c = 1.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo R_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ΔR_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo change ΔR_c"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "dF_c_vs_R_c",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Indirect shortwave forcing ΔF_c (W/m²) as a function of background cloud albedo R_c. Same parabolic shape as ΔR_c — forcing is most negative at R_c = 0.5.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_c",
                                "label": "Cloud albedo R_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ΔF_c",
                                "label": "Indirect forcing ΔF_c (W/m²)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "forcing_sensitivity_to_cloud_fraction",
                    "description": "Indirect forcing ΔF_c as a function of cloud fraction A_c at fixed Δln_N = ln(1.3) and R_c = 0.5. The linear dependence on A_c reflects that indirect forcing is proportional to the fraction of sky covered — more cloud means more total forcing. Covers the realistic range A_c ∈ [0.1, 1.0].",
                    "parameters": {
                        "F_0": 1370.0,
                        "T_a": 0.76,
                        "R_c": 0.5,
                        "Δln_N": 0.26236426446749106
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "A_c",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.1,
                                    "stop": 1.0,
                                    "count": 40,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dF_c_vs_A_c",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Indirect forcing ΔF_c (W/m²) as a function of cloud fraction A_c. Linear relationship — at A_c = 0.6 (global mean) ΔF_c ≈ −10.4 W/m².",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "A_c",
                                "label": "Cloud fraction A_c"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ΔF_c",
                                "label": "Indirect forcing ΔF_c (W/m²)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
